[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man dies in Stretford sheltered housing blaze

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man aged in his 70s has died in a fire at a flat within a sheltered and retirement housing complex in Stretford, Manchester.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The fire was at Wellington House on Sandy Lane at about 16:00 BST on Saturday.
Six firefighters in breathing apparatus entered the property. A man was pronounced dead at the scene.
A Greater Manchester Fire and Rescue Service spokesman said an investigation was under way.
Johnnie Johnson Housing Trust which runs the property said in a statement resident wellbeing and safety was a priority.
Some residents at the complex have been re-housed temporarily, it added.
Chief executive Paul Dolan said:"We send out our condolences to the families and friends of our tenant who has tragically lost his life in the incident.
"We are working closely with the emergency services to establish exactly what happened and to ensure residents can return to their homes as soon as it is safe to do so."
